          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "hello there.. my experience with HEM Gurukul.. off late from few years I have not been keeping well and sort have be stuck to my room and my bed, to make things worst than worst my husband incurred heavy losses in his business so as to we are yet not able to come out of it.. I am narrating the above becoz I want to explain how difficult it was for my son to get thru.. but HEM GURUKUL and the teachers are blessings to us and many parents and students like us. Principal Dr Ms Priti Manekar is more than anything a person could ask for her/his child, she understands and encourages students and takes them ahead...\nMy special and heartfelt gratitude to Rekha Ma'am, she is a second mother to her class students. I have experienced her dedication and efforts for the students and the care she has for them, she stands strong like a mountain behind her students and makes sure they put their efforts too.. my son has cleared his 10th exams today and that too only becoz of her. he was a weak student and she would make the bunch of weak students to sit with her in lab or in the teacher's room and help them understand the subject and the issues faced.. she has done a lot for the students and she deserves tons and tons of salutation🙏🙏🙏. once again thanku HEM GURUKUL and the teachers for your unseen yet very valuable contribution to our kids..\nHryan's mother\nSwati Choudhari Naik",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
